AGI - The Prosecutor of the Republic of Biella has notified today to the deputy of Brothers of Italy Emanuele&nbsp;Pozzolo&nbsp; the notice of conclusion of the preliminary investigations for the events of last New Year in Rosazza, where a blow started from the revolver of ownership of the parliamentarian injured a man of 31 years, Luca Campana. In the act, the Prosecutor contests a&nbsp;Pozzolo&nbsp; the crimes of blown lesions, illegal port of firearm and ammunition in public or open to the public, omitted custody of weapons and warnings/explosions dangerous. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Explains the head prosecutor of the Republic of Biella Teresa Angela Camelio: "Since the acquisition of the summary witness information" by the magistrates and carabinieri of the Andorno Micca municipality in the province of Biella, "the reconducibility of the provisionally contested crimes was emerging (personal injury, omitted custody of weapons and dangerous ignitions/explosions) to on.&nbsp;Pozzolo". The Member was then enrolled in the investigation register. The subsequent examinations, by the Stub performed by the Investigative Nucleus of the Carabinieri of Biella su&nbsp;Pozzolo&nbsp; and in the premises of the Pro Loco of Rosazza, to the subsequent technical investigations carried out in contradictory with the defense from the Ris Laboratory of Parma " have confirmed - adds the prosecutor - the initial hypothesis and have excluded the eventual involvement of third persons". It also confirms important by ballistic technical advice, carried out by the expert Raffaella Sorropago, who, still says the Prosecutor, "has ascertained the full overlap of the story of people informed about the facts and in particular those of the offended person and did not find the alternative reconstruction originally provided by the on.&nbsp;Pozzolo&nbsp; at the time of the facts". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
According to the Prosecutor of the Republic of Biella Teresa Angela Camelio, the in-depth investigations also revealed other profiles of possible crimes. "The gun from which the blow was exploded - the magistrate explains - could not be carried in public place and/or open to the public, as it was held exclusively in collection regime". Finally, Camelio concludes "it emerged that even the ammunition held by on.&nbsp;Pozzolo&nbsp; at the time of the shoot could not be brought in public and/or open to the public as 'expansive' and, therefore, returning to the so-called "war munition". The whole of the cases found led to the formulation of the various hypotheses of crime. According to the Criminal Procedure Code,&nbsp;Pozzolo&nbsp; it will now have twenty days of time to deliver memories, produce documents, deposit documentation relating to investigations of the defender, and also to issue statements or ask to be questioned. It will then be the prosecutor to make the request for referral to judgment, on which he will decide the judge of preliminary investigations. &nbsp;
